{
  "stem": "19690.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 459.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We are now in France, you have to learn French.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So gradually, we started learning French, we started-- we learned some other things to keep us busy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The other thing, my father was in [INAUDIBLE] D-- Barrack 13 I think-- and we had free go between the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I could visit my father anytime I wanted to.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And very frequently, my cousin and I would go visit our fathers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And once in a while, the mothers could go on certain days or with passes to go see the fathers or vice versa.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this was always a big occasion.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I would be with my father at least two or three times a day-- a week-- to visit.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The death rate in the camp was awful.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "People died every night.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And what us children started to discover was that in the morning, a truck would pull up and pick up the dead people from the hospital barracks and then that later that morning, that same truck would come and deliver the bread and the meat and the foods and everything else in the camp with the same drivers.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Once a very close friend of our family died-- I do not remember who it was-- and my mother insisted that I go with her to the funeral.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The cemetery was at the end of the camp and we walked there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It had not been raining that day, so it was relatively dry.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they had a makeshift casket, and being a young, curious child, I looked into the grave.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the grave was filled to within about a foot from the top with water from the ground.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the bodies-- the caskets-- were just laid into the water and then the whole thing was covered with dirt.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
